Service Cloud Voice Planning Checklist

Before setting up your Voice contact center, take care of essential planning steps. These steps highlight best practices for using Voice and help you understand what to expect during your Voice rollout.

This feature is available with these telephony models:

SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH AMAZON CONNECT
SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY FROM AMAZON CONNECT
SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY

Step 1: Review Voice’s key concepts and limitations. Understand the terms we use when talking about telephony, and read through the Voice limits and limitations.

Step 2: Choose a telephony model. Decide whether to use the out-of-the-box Amazon Connect telephony, work with your own telephony provider, or integrate an existing Amazon Connect instance with Voice.

Step 3: Consider your service limits. If your contact center will use Amazon Connect telephony, decide whether to increase your Amazon service limits.

Step 4: Plan your phone number porting. Decide whether and how to use your existing phone number or numbers in your new contact center.

Step 5: Design your environment and testing strategy. Decide how many sandbox orgs you need.

Step 6: Review networking requirements. If your contact center will use Amazon Connect telephony, review AWS’s networking guidance.

Step 7: Plan your routing requirements. Consider your current routing logic and how to improve it using Amazon Connect routing profiles and queues.

After completing these planning steps, start your setup by choosing your Service Cloud Voice telephony model.
title: Service Cloud Voice Planning Checklist
